    "analysis": "We have completed metric and trace anomaly detection. Metrics show many small, low-frequency breaches (mostly 2 points) and no single large (>50%) magnitude KPI failure. Traces show moderate-to-large relative spikes in from_frontend duration_p95 for several services (notably shippingservice-0 and adservice-0 with ratios up to ~3.5–5x). Error logs are heavily concentrated on frontend pods (frontend-2/0/1) with earliest errors right after window start (≈2022-03-21 02:30:06–02:30:10 +08). According to the diagnosis rules, when multiple container-level faults exist we should use traces and logs to select the most downstream faulty component in the call chain. To decide whether the failure is caused by frontends themselves or by downstream services (adservice, shippingservice-0 or shippingservice2-0), we need concrete error messages from the frontend error logs and a per-minute error count series to see when frontend errors began and whether they coincide with trace latency/trace anomalies. Therefore the next atomic step is to inspect error_logs for frontend-0/1/2 inside the incident window to retrieve per-minute error counts and earliest sample messages (compact).",
